        "text": "Played with it more, it's quite fun.\n\nTook the liberty of plugging taka in a new answer to <@U01ULCCJB7X>'s 3yo question <https:\/\/langdev.stackexchange.com\/questions\/1093\/should-a-concatenative-language-use-prefix-or-postfix-term-ordering\/|Should a concatenative language use prefix or postfix term ordering?>\nI really like uiua & taka's top-down right-to-left order as a new local optimum!\n\n(I'm ambivalent about inline `.` ; I feel it requires too much mental jumping from the reader, losing some of the 1:1 I find attractive in polish notation.  YMMV.  Formally `.` is same as a newline right? Maybe too much Python trained me to look differently at vertical \"statements\" vs. horizontal \"expressions\"...)",
