                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Running parallel dataflow is not useful just for exploiting hardware. If a task is doing async IO (e.g. a http request) you get parallel IO which has value even on a single CPU in languages.\n\nI am using papermill for retraining machine learning models! the parameter is the S3 file location to load the (latest) data! Very useful technique for productionizing notebooks."
                            }
